@vevebrain @thedigitalvee Pending transaction, order by highest priority fee, then put yours through based on that

@vevebrain @thedigitalvee At the end of the day, you're trying to incentivize your transactions from being picked up, but you're only competing against other transactions being directed to that contract. Formula is to only beat other pending transactions for that contract.

Putting the finishing touches on a custom nft bot to help with in-demand drops. No need to overspend on gas because of FOMO, the math is clear. Just need to have it automated so you're not fumbling come drop time, trying to boost your tx #NFT
For anyone wondering,  don't try to cancel your nft minting transaction after the drop is sold out. You'd be jus throwing gas away. #NFTdrop

@thedigitalvee To elaborate, the trick isn't really to just go wild on gas just to guarantee an NFT, but to find the spot where your transaction will get processed before any other transactions for that particular contract #NFTCommmunity  #NFTdrop #NFT
@thedigitalvee I might have a tool available soon to automate all of this, and to minimize the amount of gas that you have to spend...

But go to that same url for a non minted token number, like 9999, and you won't get any info. Same system is put in place on their frontend that shows the minted pfp's and their attributes.
Ideally I would have liked to see the attributes being hosted on ipfs as well, but ...

How did they do it ? Hosted an api with a connection to their contract on the backend, that verified the token was minted first before serving the json. Look at a random tokenId like :https://t.co/ntzDpTv7u1
Shows all the attributes, then links to ipfs for the image.
